content:
Please identify the independent clause in the following sentence and highlight it in a Latex document:
\begin{center}
Although the sun shone brightly, the wind blew coldly.
\end{center}

To identify the independent clause in the sentence "Although the sun shone brightly, the wind blew coldly," we need to find the part of the sentence that can stand alone as a complete sentence. 

In this case, the independent clause is "the wind blew coldly." It can stand alone as a complete sentence. The other part, "Although the sun shone brightly," is a dependent clause because it cannot stand alone as a complete sentence.

Here is how you can highlight the independent clause in a LaTeX document:

```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{xcolor}

\begin{document}

\begin{center}
Although the sun shone brightly, \textcolor{red}{the wind blew coldly}.
\end{center}

\end{document}
```

In this LaTeX code, the independent clause "the wind blew coldly" is highlighted in red using the `xcolor` package. You can change the color as needed.
